# Enforce Unix LF line endings for all text files.
# Prevents Windows Git (core.autocrlf=true) from injecting CRLF into
# Dockerfiles and shell scripts, which causes \r: command not found
# errors inside Linux Docker containers.
#
# Reference: docs/Architecture.md §6 — Environment & Configuration

* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicitly mark binary files so Git never touches their line endings
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.svg binary
*.pdf binary
*.docx binary
*.xlsx binary
*.pptx binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.otf binary
*.eot binary
*.zip binary
*.tar binary
*.gz binary
